The paper focuses on visual tracking using deep neural networks, specifically Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Siamese Networks. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel tracker that combines CNNs and cross-correlation operators, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also evaluates its proposed method on various datasets, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on real-time performance and tracking accuracy suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
